faq.name.aec:
An **Area Effect Cloud** is an invisible entity with no gravity, no model and almost no hitbox. It was frequently used as marker entity from 1.9 to 1.16; it was made redundant by the introduction of Marker from 1.17 onwards. Despite this, Area Effect Clouds remain popular for displaying floating text (aka "holograms"), and they also come with a built-in self-destruction timer.
Sample command: `/summon area_effect_cloud ~ ~ ~ {Duration:2147483647,CustomName:'"<Name>"',CustomNameVisible:true}`
<https://minecraft.wiki/w/Lingering_Potion#Area_Effect_Cloud>
faq.name.datapack:
A datapack is created by placing a "data" folder and a "pack.mcmeta" file into the same folder.
Datapack structure:
```📄pack.mcmeta
🖼️pack.png
📂data
  📂namespace
    📁advancements
    📁chat_type
    📁datapacks
    📁dimension
    📁dimension_type
    📁functions
    📁loot_tables
    📁predicates
    📁recipes
    📁structures
    📂tags
      📁blocks
      📁entity_types
      📁fluids
      📁functions
      📁game_events
      📁items
      📂worldgen
        📁biome
        📁configured_structure_feature
    📂worldgen
      📁biome
      📁configured_carver
      📁configured_feature
      📁density_function
      📁flat_level_generator_preset
      📁noise
      📁noise_settings
      📁structure
      📁structure_set
      📁world_preset
      📁placed_feature
      📁configured_structure_feature
      📁configured_surface_builder
      📁processor_list
      📁template_pool
```<https://minecraft.wiki/w/Tutorials/Creating_a_data_pack>
faq.name.log: `latest.log` is a text document found in the `.minecraft/logs` folder. It logs various game information starting from the last time you launched the game, including command outputs, chat history and datapack error outputs.
faq.name.marker:
A **Marker** is an invisible entity that only exists on the server side, introduced in 1.17 specifically to be used by commands and in mapmaking. It can store any arbitrary NBT data in its unique `{data}` NBT tag.
Markers cannot have the `{Passengers}` NBT, and it will not display CustomName even `{CustomNameVisible}` is set to true.
Sample command: `/summon marker ~ ~ ~ {data:{YourNBTHere:""}}`
https://minecraft.wiki/w/Marker
faq.name.save:
The contents of a typical world folder (found in `.minecraft/saves`) is as follows:```📁advancements <-- Advancement progress of each player, one file per player

📂data
  📄chunks.dat <-- Forceloaded chunks
  📄map_<id>.dat <-- The <id>th map in the world, starting with 0
  📄raids.dat <-- Ongoing raids in the overworld dimension
  📄scoreboard.dat <-- Scoreboards and teams

📁datapacks <-- Put your datapacks here

📂DIM1 <-- Data about the End dimension
  📂data
    📄raids_end.dat <-- Ongoing raids in the End
  📁entities <-- Entities in the End
  📁poi <-- Points of interest in the End
  📁region <-- All blocks in the End, one file per chunk

📂DIM-1 <-- Data about the Nether dimension
  📂data
    📄raids_nether.dat <-- Ongoing raids in the Nether
  📁entities <-- Entities in the Nether
  📁poi <-- Points of interest in the Nether
  📁region <-- All chunks in the Nether, one file per chunk

📁entities <-- Entities in the Overworld

📁playerdata <-- NBT tags of all players, one file per player

📁poi <-- Points of interest in the Overworld

📁region <-- All blocks in the Overworld, one file per chunk

📁stats <-- Statistics of all players

🖼️icon.png <-- The icon that displays in the world selection menu

📄level.dat <-- Everything else about the world, including world name, version, game rules, border size, weather etc.```<https://minecraft.wiki/w/Java_Edition_level_format>
